&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-bridge-lab-screening-and-lab-the-inspection-from-a24-tickets-474210736077" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REGISTER HERE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Forum has partnered with The Bridge Lab and&amp;nbsp;A24 to present a special Harlem screening of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The Inspection&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://a24films.com/films/inspection" target="_blank"&gt;The Inspection&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;--&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;Elegance Bratton&amp;rsquo;s deeply moving film inspired by his own story -- a young, gay Black man, rejected by his mother and with few options for his future, decides to join the Marines, doing whatever it takes to succeed in a system that would cast him aside. But even as he battles deep-seated prejudice and the grueling routines of basic training, he finds unexpected camaraderie, strength, and support in this new community, giving him a hard-earned sense of belonging that will shape his identity and forever change his life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This screening is a part of The Bridge Lab&amp;#39;s programming for educational opportunities, employment entry points and advocacy in the entertainment industry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.thebridgelabnyc.org/" target="_blank"&gt;The Bridge Lab&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;helps youth and young adults from under represented communities bridge gaps between their talent and hard to access information and networks.&lt;/p&gt;

