&lt;p&gt;Please join us for a screening of &lt;em&gt;Bad Roads &lt;/em&gt;(2020) by &lt;strong&gt;Natalya Vorozhbit&lt;/strong&gt;, the final screening of the Fall 2022 Harriman Film Series &lt;em&gt;Warning Signs, &lt;/em&gt;which explores the female optics on the threshold of the present-day war in Ukraine. &lt;em&gt;Bad Roads &lt;/em&gt;brings together four stories set in the conflict zone of Ukraine before the recent full-scale military invasion. Resisting coherent narrative structure, the movie follows fraught everyday encounters which sometimes turn into scenes of violence. In 2021, &lt;em&gt;Bad Roads&lt;/em&gt; was selected as Ukraine&amp;rsquo;s submission for the Academy Awards Best International Feature Film. Screening organized with participation of &lt;a href="https://slavic.columbia.edu/content/serhii-tereshchenko" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Serhii&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tereschenko&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Graduate Student in the Department of Slavic Languages. Moderated by &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://harriman.columbia.edu/person/mark-lipovetsky/"&gt;Mark Lipovetsky&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;a href="https://harriman.columbia.edu/person/tatiana-efremova/"&gt;T&lt;strong&gt;anya Efremova&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
